choices.text: making people stop staring at me in the stores and academy and work whenever I’m trying to reside a normal life.. I’ve even had people follow me home from from the mall.. I’ve tried making human barriers but that doesn’t always work, today I was walking passed a store not for the first time but I must have stood out before this. Suddenly the new employee decided to call out to me “excuse me miss! You dropped something!” it was a lady this time it was very patronizing. I informed the lady I didn’t drop anything and I continued to walk by this store but suddenly this untrained employee decided to block my way in, I told him I’m going home so he would let me past and he tried grabbing me shoulder it was very frustrating. I repeatedly told him to leave me alone or I’d actually make a scene but he stood by me annoyed so I remembered how many times we call police over petty small missing items they don’t show up so I didn’t bother.. the employee just kept insisting he wasn’t done talking to me and I had to reassure him I was calm and that I don’t carry weapons, so in a sarcastic voice he then offerend to walk me the way I was already walking home..” he’s the only employee allowed to speak to me that means” I finally agreed to walk home with him and tea whomever else he find it… Go back to paying caretaker when in comes to female teenagers from my culture,
